clause.text:
conduct regular,
				ongoing monitoring of the implementation of the hospital-wide staffing plan for
				nursing services furnished in the hospital;

subparagraph.text:
take into account
				contextual issues affecting nurse staffing and the delivery of care, including
				architecture and geography of the environment and available technology;

take into account
				the level of education, training, and experience of those registered nurses
				providing direct patient care;

take into account
				unit and facility level staffing, quality and patient outcome data, and
				national comparisons, as available;

shall not preempt
				any registered-nurse staffing levels established under State law or regulation;
				and

